reviews_data.review_text: I placed an order online and ordered 2 drinks and a swig coffee cup coozie. When I arrived at the window I was told they were out of items for my drink I ordered, I kindly said that’s okay and to give me anything sweet. The staff then asked me what the swig coozie was.. there was multiple pink ones hanging in the window of the drive through. I ordered a different color and asked if I could get the one I ordered. I was then told they didn’t have it and the staff walked away. I waited for my drinks and was told to have a nice day. I asked if I could get a refund for the $15 dollar swig coozie and was told “yeah”. No questions were asked. The girl then said have a nice day and tried to walk away- I asked when I would receive my refund and she said “depends on your bank” and closed the window and walked away. At this point I was going to be late for work so I had to leave. I only have my online order that states I ordered and paid for the swig coozie, that I never received. I still have not received a refund and this was over 2 weeks ago. I’m very disappointed in this service. I spent over $36 for 2 drinks and no swig coozie.

reviews_data.review_text: The coffee and food are great. The customer service however needs to be improved. At first I used the drive through but it would take a long time to receive my coffee even though I was the only car there. I started ordering ahead but for some reason it takes even longer than ordering at the drive thru. The teenagers or young adults  who were in charge of my order were dressed like they just got out of bed, unprofessional.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are sorry to hear you didn't have a great experience at our store. Can you email us at customerrelations@cariboucoffee.com so we can follow up with you? Please provide your Caribou Perks account information if you're a member. Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text:
**editing my review- customer service sent me a gift card to rectify the coffee below. This time I got a hot campfire latte- and asked for half sweet. The flavor was good, super liked the marshmallow. Was still very sweet much on the sweet side though. Next time I will ask for 1/4 sweet, and fingers crossed the sweetness will be the right balance!

Could we normalize lattes without a pound of sugar? I got the northern light latte, thinking it meant light coffee. I should have asked or searched the menu first, because it meant that they use lite sugar free syrup. I asked for a half a pump.

I like flavor, a little bit of sweetness, but this latte tastes like the iced coffee version of sweet tea on steroids.

It’s so undrinkable. I wish that I could actually taste the coffee, but the only thing I can taste is syrupy sweet blasphemy.

I’m so so disappointed I didn’t taste it before leaving, and that I wasted 6.50 on a drink I can’t force myself to drink.

The girl at the drive thru was super pleasant and sweet though.
reviews_data.owner_answer: We are sorry to hear you didn't have a great experience at our store. Can you email us at customerrelations@cariboucoffee.com so we can follow up with you? Please provide your Caribou Perks account information if you're a member. Thank you!

reviews_data.review_text:
We stopped by the drive-thru on a Saturday morning. There was no one in line ahead of us, no cars behind us, and the place looked completely empty inside. We ordered two coffees, a blueberry muffin (asked to have it warmed up), and a bagel. Instead, they gave us a blueberry bagel, the muffin was cold, and it was basically 90% sugar - it went straight into the trash. Completely inedible.

They also messed up our coffee order multiple times, and neither of the TWO employees could figure out what they had given us. The service was terrible, and on top of that, they expect tips?

Dear customers, this is just a place where you’re grabbing a coffee - don’t leave a tip and don’t support tipping for service like this especially in the coffee places. Drinks are 70% sugar.
Good morning to the two employees who couldn’t get a single simple order right. Again, we were the ONLY car in line. One car, one easy order, 10min wait. We won’t be back.

reviews_data.owner_answer: Thanks for letting us know you had a great time. Looking forward to your next visit!

reviews_data.review_text: Caribou is my favorite coffee place. I was very excited to see one down in this area. The baristas are very nice and friendly. I went in to order so I could leisurely enjoy my coffee. I ordered 3 drinks and an egg souffle. They did not have a coffee carrier for me as they had run out of them. They have a VERY small area with 3 tables that are close together. Not conducive to have a leisurely coffee. They have a very large outdoor seating area under a roof and a drive thru. While most coffee places want people to stay and enjoy, this Caribou does not seem to want that. Since it's been in the 90s the past several weeks and I work outdoors, I did not want to sit outside to enjoy my coffee. While service is slow, the employees are friendly and nice so I can overlook slow service when the servers are pleasant. Drive-thru or inside, you will have to wait a little, but you'll be fine. The only disappointing thing for me is the layout of this particular Caribou which is a corporate decision, not the people who are working there. I appreciate the people who work there who are so pleasant.
How long has this Caribou been open? I love Caribou coffee!

Again I went and they didn’t add the sweet cold foam and my boyfriend asked for no ice which they forgot as well. The “sweet cold foam” had no flavor all it felt like was foam. Very disappointed I thought this was going to be my new favorite place.

reviews_data.review_text:
This location opened on Friday May 2, 2024 and is the first location in the Monroe area. This was my first time trying caribou coffee and the experience was great.

We got a nitro high rise and a vanilla shaken espresso with oat milk. For our food we got a chorizo breakfast burrito and a bacon egg and cheese bagel. The food portions were significantly more than Starbucks as well.

The staff was friendly and knowledgeable about what caribou offers and the store was tidy and clean apart from boxed supplies being stored by our table which is no big deal.

I would definitely come here again!

reviews_data.review_text:
This location opened on Friday May 2, 2024 and is the first location in the Monroe area. This was my first time trying caribou coffee and the experience was great.

We got a nitro high rise and a vanilla shaken espresso with oat milk. For our food we got a chorizo breakfast burrito and a bacon egg and cheese bagel. The food portions were significantly more than Starbucks as well.

The staff was friendly and knowledgeable about what caribou offers and the store was tidy and clean apart from boxed supplies being stored by our table which is no big deal.

I would definitely come here again!
